        "subject": "LU-15340 llite: Reuse existing inode for io warning print",
        "message": "LU-15340 llite: Reuse existing inode for io warning print\n\nReference vop_inode before storign it to ensure it never goes away,\npass it down to ll_dirty_page_discard_warn instead of the vmpage,\nthis way we are sure it won't disappear from under us.\nThis should also solve the livelock situation where dput in\nll_dirty_page_discard_warn results in the final iput on the inode\nthat the page is attached to (which I am not sure how it happens\nin the first place since it's supposed to be same as vop_inode\neven though the comment at the start of vvp_vmpage_error seems to\nimply that DIRECT_IO might point to a different inode than the\npage inode - but in reality I guess in case of direct io the\n\"page inode\" is some garbage considering that the page is a\nuserspace buffer so we are more coorect to use the actual inode\nfrom IO/vvp object)\n\nChange-Id: I68a1c3b3aa059e968d09adbd98cd093c7e832473\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
